  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Slice the baguette in half lengthwise and place on a baking sheet.",
    "Spread the pizza sauce evenly over the baguette, leaving a small border around the edges.",
    "Top the sauce with the mozzarella cheese, caramelized onions, crispy bacon, rosemary, garlic, and red pepper flakes.",
    "Drizzle with a small amount of olive oil to bring everything together.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for a few minutes before slicing and serving.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
